description: Get ready for an unforgettable evening on July 19th aboard the M.V. ABITIBI! Join us for a spectacular dinner cruise featuring the Annual Vancouver Fireworks Show. This extraordinary night is your exclusive invitation to experience the magical combination of fine dining and an electrifying fireworks display. Revel in the unique atmosphere while taking in Vancouver's breathtaking vistas - a truly unparalleled experience. Admiral's Boarding commences at 6:30 PM , allowing you ample time to settle in for our 4-hour journey, enhanced with an additional hour for boarding. We set sail promptly at 7:30 PM, promising an evening filled with unforgettable memories. Live music and DJ to keep the vibe energetic On-deck bar offering a range of premium drinks. Professional photographers to capture your magical moments. A tantalizing double-entrée buffet-style dinner, including the Admiral's Fleet Dinner Menu and a dessert buffet.( Dinner Included With Ticket - See Menu Below For more info) **Please let us know ahead of time if you require special dietary instructions** Experience the fireworks from an incredible viewpoint as you enjoy your favorite drinks and dance to top-40 music. Please note that an adult must accompany passengers under age. Book now to secure your place for this sensational summer event!

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Ready to get your hips moving, feet stomping, and heart pumping to the rollicking rhythms of la música latina? Whether you're a complete newbie or just looking to sharpen your skills, our fun and friendly classes will have you grooving in no time. Bonus : Your first class is absolutely free! Feel the energy, embrace the music, and unleash the dancer within! No partner? No problem—you’ll meet new friends while learning new moves. Two left feet? Don’t worry! We’ll have you grooving with confidence before you know it, and wondering why you didn’t start sooner.
location: 345 West Broadway, Vancouver, BC V5Y 1P8
price: First class free, $30 for 3 one-hour classes, $50 for 6 one-hour classes, $15 per one-hour class drop-in

Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha Cha - Intermediate/ Advanced
description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

dance_style: bachata, cha cha, dance, merengue, salsa
description:
We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson
Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight
Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST

event_name: VS and Pacific Opera Victoria at The Butchart Gardens
description: Led by Maestro Giuseppe Pietraroia, the Victoria Symphony performs at The Butchart Gardens alongside the Pacific Opera Victoria Chorus, soprano Lauren Margison, tenor Adam Luther, and pianist Patrick Cao.
source: Groovin' to Victoria's Live Music Scene | Tourism Victoria
location: The Butchart Gardens

description: Maestro Giuseppe Pietraroia leads the Victoria Symphony with trumpet soloist Ryan Cole in a program including Mozart’s Overture to The Magic Flute, Neruda’s Trumpet Concerto, and Dvořák’s Symphony No. 5.
source: Groovin' to Victoria's Live Music Scene | Tourism Victoria
location: Christ Church Cathedral

description: Victoria Symphony returns to Qualicum Beach with Maestro Giuseppe Pietraroia and trumpet soloist Ryan Cole performing Mozart’s Magic Flute overture, Neruda’s Trumpet Concerto, and Dvořák’s Symphony No. 5.
source: Groovin' to Victoria's Live Music Scene | Tourism Victoria
location: Qualicum Beach Civic Centre

event_name: The National Youth Orchestra of Canada
description: Conductor Naomi Woo leads the National Youth Orchestra of Canada in works by Nicholas Denton Protsack, featuring violinist Justin Saulnier in Prokofiev’s Second Violin Concerto, and Shostakovich’s Symphony No. 10.
source: Groovin' to Victoria's Live Music Scene | Tourism Victoria
location: Christ Church Cathedral

event_name: Celeigh Cardinal & Shawnee Kish with The National Youth Orchestra of Canada
description: JUNO-nominated vocalists Celeigh Cardinal and Shawnee Kish join The National Youth Orchestra of Canada under Naomi Woo for a genre-defying outdoor concert at Victoria’s Inner Harbour.
source: Groovin' to Victoria's Live Music Scene | Tourism Victoria
location: Inner Harbour

description: Principal Pops Conductor Sean O’Loughlin leads the Victoria Symphony on a floating barge with favorites like Shostakovich’s Festival Overture, Holst’s Jupiter, Star Wars, and concludes with Tchaikovsky’s 1812 Overture and Amazing Grace with fireworks.

description: Young people aged between 8 and 11 years of age are welcome to attend. Daily Junior Summer Camp activities will include dance classes, crafts, chalk drawings outdoors, outdoor games together with some challenges over the week such as creating a dance, compiling a word board, word searches and maybe even a quiz. Refreshments and snacks will be provided each day between the activities. Young people can either be dropped off at workshops by a parent/guardian who is attending the Adult Summer School or parents who are not attending the Adult Summer School may drop young people off at the workshops on a daily basis and collect them at lunch time each day. If a young person is resident with parent/guardian then the parent/guardian will be responsible for the young person outside of the designated workshop times. These classes aimed at young people run alongside the usual Summer School schedule, allowing parents and their children to attend the event together. Programme to follow.
source: JMMF | Royal Scottish Country Dance Society
location: Location to be announced

description: Designed for Young People aged between 12 and 17 years of age. Young dancers between 12 – 17 yrs will attend a class of their ability along with the other Summer School dancers. There will be opportunities for this age group to get together with peers in some afternoons. Young people can either be dropped off at workshops by a parent/guardian who is attending the Adult Summer School or parents who are not attending the Adult Summer School may drop interested young people off at the workshops on a daily basis and collect them at lunch time each day. If a young person is resident with parent/guardian then the parent/guardian will be responsible for the young person outside of the designated workshop times.
source: JMMF | Royal Scottish Country Dance Society

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison.
